# Sandbox Configuration Guide

The sandbox restricts Agent terminal commands to prevent unauthorized file access and network activity. Available on macOS (v2.0+) and Linux (v2.3.0+). Granular network and filesystem controls added in Cursor 2.5.

## Default Behavior

| Access Type | Default |
|-------------|---------|
| File access | Read: full filesystem. Write: workspace directories only. |
| Network access | Blocked entirely |
| Temporary files | Full access to `/tmp/` |

## Configuration File (`sandbox.json`)

Place `sandbox.json` in either or both locations:

| Location | Scope | Priority |
|----------|-------|----------|
| `~/.cursor/sandbox.json` | All workspaces (per-user) | Lower |
| `.cursor/sandbox.json` | Single workspace (per-repo) | Higher |

Both are optional. When both exist, per-repo settings take priority.

## Network Policy

### Allow specific domains (recommended)

```json
{
  "networkPolicy": {
    "default": "deny",
    "allow": [
      "registry.npmjs.org",
      "pypi.org",
      "*.githubusercontent.com"
    ]
  }
}
```

### Allow all network

```json
{
  "networkPolicy": {
    "default": "allow"
  }
}
```

### Pattern syntax

| Format | Example | Matches |
|--------|---------|---------|
| Exact domain | `"registry.npmjs.org"` | That exact host |
| Wildcard | `"*.example.com"` | Any subdomain of `example.com`, including itself |
| CIDR | `"10.0.0.0/8"` | Any IP in that range |

**Rules**: Deny always beats allow. Matching is domain/IP only (URL paths ignored). Private/RFC 1918 addresses and cloud metadata endpoints (`169.254.169.254`) blocked by default.

## Schema Reference

### Top-level fields

| Field | Type | Default | Description |
|-------|------|---------|-------------|
| `type` | string | `"workspace_readwrite"` | `"workspace_readwrite"`, `"workspace_readonly"`, or `"insecure_none"` |
| `additionalReadwritePaths` | `string[]` | `[]` | Extra paths the agent can read and write |
| `additionalReadonlyPaths` | `string[]` | `[]` | Extra paths the agent can read |
| `disableTmpWrite` | boolean | `false` | Remove default write access to `/tmp/` |
| `enableSharedBuildCache` | boolean | `false` | Share npm/pip/cargo caches between sandboxed and unsandboxed runs |

### networkPolicy object

| Field | Type | Default | Description |
|-------|------|---------|-------------|
| `default` | `"allow"` or `"deny"` | `"deny"` | Action when no rule matches |
| `allow` | `string[]` | `[]` | Domains/IPs to allow |
| `deny` | `string[]` | `[]` | Domains/IPs to deny (highest priority, always blocks) |

## Full Example

A full-stack project needing packages, containers, database, and shared paths:

```json
{
  "networkPolicy": {
    "default": "deny",
    "allow": [
      "registry.npmjs.org",
      "registry.yarnpkg.com",
      "pypi.org",
      "files.pythonhosted.org",
      "*.docker.io",
      "ghcr.io",
      "*.googleapis.com"
    ],
    "deny": [
      "*.internal.corp.example.com"
    ]
  },
  "additionalReadwritePaths": [
    "/home/me/.docker"
  ],
  "additionalReadonlyPaths": [
    "/opt/shared/design-tokens"
  ],
  "enableSharedBuildCache": true
}
```

## Policy Merge Order

```
per-user  <  per-repo  <  team-admin  <  hardcoded
(lowest)                                (highest)
```

- Restrictive booleans (`disableTmpWrite`): `true` wins
- `networkPolicy.default`: `"deny"` wins over `"allow"`
- Deny lists: always unioned
- Allow lists: unioned, unless team-admin allowlist present (replaces union)
- Paths: unioned across all sources

## Protected Paths (Always Write-Protected)

These are never writable regardless of `sandbox.json`:
- `.cursorignore`, `.code-workspace`
- `.git/hooks/**`, `.git/config`, `.git/info/attributes`
- `.vscode/**`
- `.cursor/*.json`, `.cursor/**/*.json`, `.cursor/.workspace-trusted`

**Writable exceptions**: `.cursor/rules/`, `.cursor/commands/`, `.cursor/worktrees/`, `.cursor/skills/`, `.cursor/agents/`

## Editor Settings

Configure in Settings > Cursor Settings > Agents > Auto-Run:

| Setting | Options |
|---------|---------|
| Auto-Run Mode | Run in Sandbox / Ask Every Time / Run Everything |
| Auto-Run Network Access | sandbox.json Only / sandbox.json + Defaults / Allow All |
| Command Allowlist | Commands that skip sandbox |
| MCP Allowlist | MCP tools that skip sandbox |

## Enterprise Controls

Admins on Enterprise plan can enforce from [dashboard](https://cursor.com/dashboard):
- Sandbox mode enforcement
- Network allowlists/denylists (team-wide)
- Terminal command allowlists
- MCP tool protection
- File deletion protection

## When Sandbox Blocks a Command

| Option | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| Skip | Cancel, let Agent try alternatives |
| Run | Execute without sandbox restrictions |
| Add to allowlist | Run unrestricted and auto-approve for future use |

